400,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-06 03:19:18+00:00,17867599,fprimex/zdesk,614790,fprimex,,,125065939,169208420,"Hi,

There is no need to transform the response using `response.json()`. What is returned from the `search` method will be a `dict` corresponding to the JSON that was returned by the request.

I recommend having a look at the output of `print(type(response))` and also `pprint(response)` (after doing `from pprint import pprint` of course). What you will see is that `response` is a `dict`, and that the structure of it is something like `{ 'results' : [ <result json 1>, <result json 2>, ...], <other attributes of search result json>, ...}`. So what you'll want to actually iterate over is `for result in response['results']:`, usually.

Please have a look specifically at the ""JSON Format"" and example output provided:

https://developer.zendesk.com/rest_api/docs/core/search#json-format

