With regard to your questions:

* vhacd -- Yep, testVHACD is the correct binary :) We can modify the backend to look for testVHACD as well, we'd just installed it as vhacd. I compiled it from source, but I think all the recent pre-compiled binaries should work fine.
* overrides -- If the COM is overridden, it automatically removes mass_properties from the cache, so when moment_inertia is queried, it recomputes the mass_properties with the new COM, which should return a valid inertial matrix (assuming the mesh is watertight, so the volume computation works). Ditto for density. I assumed that if you overrode those properties, you wanted mass_properties to use the overridden values.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
