714,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-24 19:52:37+00:00,50903853,AnalogJ/lexicon,891875,AnalogJ,,,334471809,399782826,"Hmm, not sure I would quite agree with that.

There are other providers which only support manipulation at the record set level rather than at the record level. 

This limited granularity is usually solved by doing a list operation, finding the current records in the record set, manipulating the set as required, and then submitting the changes to the API.
There's definitely the possibility for a race condition if another tool other than lexicon is updating the records, however it seems to be a fair trade off for not having to know all the records in the record set at runtime. 

If you are creating a Google Cloud provider, I would probably go that route if possible, just to keep all the providers consistent. 

In general I try to ensure that `create` operations are additive, and only `delete` & `update` are destructive. 

Hopefully that all makes sense?",{},OWNER,User,False
