954,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-30 16:05:37+00:00,13698035,IanHarvey/bluepy,2851928,IanHarvey,,,83113585,276103617,"> Is there any other way to get the descriptor handle and enable/disable notifications? 

Services and characteristics now have a `getDescriptors()` method (commit 5c107d1 and later). Code to use them looks something like this (see pull request #89):
```python
   char = peripheral.getCharacteristics(uuid=your_uuid_here)[0]
   ccc_desc = char.getDescriptors(forUUID=0x2902)[0]
   ccc_desc.write(b""\x01"")
```

The _sensortag.py_ code now (commit 9945d88) uses this to enable notifications on the sensortag's ""keypress"" service.
",{},,User,False
