1015,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-29 09:44:13+00:00,5488471,dsoprea/GDriveFS,715626,dsoprea,,,162869518,229309018,"So, I'm just going to take a moment and expound on how to control mimetype derivation in GDFS.

The typing process works as follows (starting [here](https://github.com/dsoprea/GDriveFS/blob/master/gdrivefs/gdfs/gdfuse.py#L292)):
1. The split_path call dissects the file-path argument. You can pass an optional type-hint in the way of a mime-type (e.g. ""Biola.docx#application+pdf"")
2. We call mimetypes.guess_type() from Python.
3. Fallback to taking the value of the `default_mimetype` configurable (""application/octet-stream"").

I had also added the ability to read a JSON-encoded dictionary of file-extension/mime-type mappings back in the very beginning, but it looks like this was never wired in. I guess it never came up. I've gone ahead and implemented this between steps (1) and (2). I committed this to the ""mimetype_overrides"" branch. If you could test it, I'd appreciate it. It's getting pretty late but I wanted to throw it out there for you without waiting, just in case you wanted it. In order to use this, pass it as an ""o"" option in the mount command: e.g. ""-o extension_mapping_filepath=/home/dustin/gdfs_mimetypes.json"". By default, the file-path is ""/etc/gdfs/extension_mapping.json"" but it is obviously only used if it exists.

Finally, the least-elegant option is to add an entry to the mime-type/extension dictionary (`default_extensions`) at the top of the `_DriveUtility` class, at the top of `utility.py`. 

Now, as far as that default-mimetype"" option that you commented it can *also* be overridden like any other option (like the above) by passing it in the mount options and assign it (""file_default_mime_type"") some other value. Note that I just committed another change that will make it `None` if you set it to empty.

I'd appreciate you testing both of these changes and getting back to me. I'll totally deimplement the default-mimetype logic. I'll have to do this a little later, but it'd be great if *you* could do this and submit a PR. Your choice. 

Thanks.
",{},,User,False
