1057,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-02 20:48:28+00:00,8842308,itamarst/crochet,6538298,mjbryant,,,188928437,264558773,"So I like your new 3-step plan - that calling `crochet.setup()` will do a PID check and reinitialize things if it's changed - but I'm not sure it'll work with the global twisted reactor. The reactor is not restartable, which is why my PR includes running a _non-global_ reactor in the crochet thread. And the fact that we have to run a non-global reactor is the reason `get_reactor` exists - other libraries that want access to the crochet-controlled reactor can no longer get a reference to it by doing `from twisted.internet import reactor`.",{},,User,False
