1243,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-24 23:44:20+00:00,46906439,diafygi/acme-tiny,4494239,pjtpj,,,184981592,255896970,"I originally used certbot in standalone mode. It turns out that this results in an authorization request with type tls-sni-01. 3 months a 1 day later (my SSL certificate expired yesterday), I tried to use acme_tiny, but my new http-01 authorization request got stuck because the status on my 3 month old tls-sni-01 request still was ""valid"". This means that the new http-01 request made by acme_tiny was forever stuck with status ""pending"" as described at  https://community.letsencrypt.org/t/stuck-at-pending-when-using-dns-challenge/19148. This code change allowed acme_tiny to continue and successfully sign my renewal certificate signing request. IMO it is a bug that the original tls-sni-01 request was valid longer than the resulting signed SSL certificate, but that is a separate issue.",{},,User,False
