1452,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-30 22:30:35+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,98275186,126509845,"Hi @JeroenNX!

It might also depend on the parser. Some parsers have a `parsed: true` setting ([ref](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-parsers-advanced.html)) which forces a column to always use parsed data.

Looking at the built-in parsers, only the ""url"" and ""image"" parsers have this flag set.

Also, it depends on the filter type. The following will use parsed data if the parser type is ""numeric"":
* Operators (e.g. `>= 10`)
* Range (e.g. `1 - 10`)

It would help me troubleshoot the issue better if you could provide an example or more details.",{},,User,False
