2917,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-03 11:33:39+00:00,3687291,maxcountryman/flask-login,522344,alanhamlett,,,187019246,258119582,"This happens to us all the time too, namespaces change in packages we depend on. Even if we add `_create_identifier` to the global namespace, there will still be incompatible versions with your library since it's already been released this way. The way we usually handle namespace changes is by gracefully handling an import error and trying the alternate namespace:

```python
try:
    from flask_login.utils import _create_identifier
except ImportError:
    from flask_login import _create_identifier
```

",{},,User,False
