3084,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-06 13:47:01+00:00,29258660,etianen/django-python3-ldap,148744,etianen,,,263439625,334759610,"Easy!

Instead of this setting:

AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS = (""django_python3_ldap.auth.LDAPBackend"",)

Use this:

AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS = (
    ""django_python3_ldap.auth.LDAPBackend"",
    ""django.contrib.auth.backends.ModelBackend"",
)

Django tries the authentication backends in order. If the user isn't found
in LDAP, it'll try in the database.

Pretty sweet! :D

