3086,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-06 01:02:42+00:00,29991779,jrief/django-sass-processor,1593486,AndreasBackx,,,136246326,230645655,"`self._source_file` is initialised when using Jinja2, but the Django Template engine doesn't use it and falls back to `self.source[0].name` which was in the code and refers to the source template file (where the tag is used). See the `SassSrcNode.source_file` property.

The Jinja2 extension simply uses the node you implemented and acts like a wrapper around it, see [`SassSrc._sass_src_support`](https://github.com/jrief/django-sass-processor/blob/master/sass_processor/jinja2/ext.py#L30-L32). I would like to help, but am leaving on vacation at the end of the week and won't be back till the end of the month unfortunately. I am happy to work on it together when I get back. There shouldn't be any issues with the Jinja2 extension as long as `SassSrcNode.render` keeps doing what it is doing right now.",{},,User,False
