3587,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-07 18:12:34+00:00,33884891,apache/incubator-airflow,29158971,jpds,47359,apache,240727817,371230900,"@dimberman Another thing which I require to be able to set with this is pod affinity[1] for a particular task.

On AWS, I have some rather compute intense tasks which need to land on large EC2 instances separate from our main cluster instances. We do this normally with this for example:

```
spec:
  affinity:
    nodeAffinity:
      requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
        nodeSelectorTerms:
        - matchExpressions:
          - key: beta.kubernetes.io/instance-type
            operator: In
            values:
            - c5.9xlarge
```

We then leverage the cluster autoscaler[2] and have an auto-scaling group which spins up a node in the right instance group[3]; the job runs and when completed, the node shutdowns down and the cluster scales down.

[1]: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python/blob/master/kubernetes/docs/V1PodSpec.md
[2]: https://github.com/kubernetes/kops/tree/master/addons/cluster-autoscaler
[3]: https://github.com/kubernetes/kops/blob/master/docs/instance_groups.md",{},NONE,User,False
