3911,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-30 18:44:39+00:00,14993021,ipython/traitlets,2397974,SylvainCorlay,230453,ipython,71962839,97916836,"- Re: pylab, then the code should probably do `default_value=None` right?
- Re: delaying default values. The main use case I have in mind is the case of an Instance trait type. 

```Python
class Foo(Widget):
    bar= Instance(Bar)
```
Then

```Python
# The following works
bar= Foo(bar=SomeBar()) 

# The following tries instantiating an invalid default value for `bar`
# even though it is not ever used
foo= Foo()  # raises TraitError
foo.bar= SomeBar()
```",{},,User,False
