Review status: all files reviewed at latest revision, 4 unresolved discussions, some commit checks failed.

---

*[system_tests/catalog_tests.py, line 33 at r3](https://reviewable.io/reviews/vmware/pyvcloud/239#-LCje-Rs3skXcqVa6V-X:-LCk477L12Xi6W8OyD85:b-m9revn) ([raw file](https://github.com/vmware/pyvcloud/blob/78bcee2f8521ca4d11e2e3edada9f2cc20eb333c/system_tests/catalog_tests.py#L33)):*
<details><summary><i>Previously, hodgesrm (Robert Hodges) wrote…</i></summary><blockquote>

this is the only case that actually uploads files, it appears. Yet it does not actually do the upload if the items already exist.  Seems as if this means much of the time we might not actually test upload.  If I'm reading the code correctly there should be a case that checks upload each time the test runs. 
</blockquote></details>

I was following the pattern we have established that don't create/upload things and reuse them if possible.
I can surely relax that for this case and create a new catalog every time this test is run, which will guarantee that the upload is triggered. :)

---

*[system_tests/catalog_tests.py, line 84 at r3](https://reviewable.io/reviews/vmware/pyvcloud/239#-LCjcmrz3ISsUGomMqiA:-LCjrDMwBqvDfZY3N1yv:b-j2r8hl) ([raw file](https://github.com/vmware/pyvcloud/blob/78bcee2f8521ca4d11e2e3edada9f2cc20eb333c/system_tests/catalog_tests.py#L84)):*
<details><summary><i>Previously, hodgesrm (Robert Hodges) wrote…</i></summary><blockquote>

Awesome comments.  If you run the test two times in rapid succession will you somehow collide with the previous uploaded catalog item?  
</blockquote></details>

The second call will fail.

Uploading an item to a catalog involves the following steps,
1. Do a POST call on vCD to let vCD know that you are trying to upload a catalog item (media / template)
2. Wait for vCD to create proper transfer folder corresponding to the catalog item. (Unfortunately this is not implemented via tasks in vCD, so we need to monitor the catalog item resource and wait for the url of catalog item to appear in the response).
3. Upload the bits to the transfer folder
4. Wait for vCD to finish importing whatever you have uploaded to transfer folder into the ESX host.

Step 1 is what guarantees that the second upload call will fail with the error message ""Item with same name exists in the catalog""

---

