4386,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-24 13:57:04+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,9541,illume,647025,pypa,144276046,274809001,"Hello.

I made a small patch here with something that works for me, but needs a bit more work after discussion: https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/pull/943

This is a solution so that the simple case works without requiring any extra parameters be used.

I modified sampleproject here: https://github.com/illume/sampleproject
Note how there is only a file `sample/sample.py` and no `__init__.py`.

This is the simplest possible package. I think this is a very important use case for many people, and I don't think find_packages() should require doing anything special with any extra parameters for this case. I've seen many people trip over this issue, since it's pretty much the simplest type of package you can make.

It works for me on the sampleproject above, and some other projects I tested. I handled the case where it ignores directories with site-packages in them (probably a venv, definitely not a package).

There are a few failing tests still. Also, I need to make it only look for namespace packages in python 3.3+

What do you think?",{},,User,False
4389,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-30 21:48:40+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,308610,jaraco,647025,pypa,144422559,203649496,"When I try to replicate your issue, I create a python2.7 env:

```
$ python -m virtualenv --python python2.7 --no-setuptools --no-pip issue525
# install distribute 0.6.24 into virtualenv
...
$ cat >> issue525/setup.py
from setuptools import setup
setup(
    name='my-project',
    version='0.1',
    install_requires=[
        'distribute==0.7.3',
        'setuptools==20.3.1',
    ],
)

$ cd issue525
$ bin/python setup.py install
...
Installed /Users/jaraco/issue525/lib/python2.7/site-packages/my_project-0.1-py2.7.egg
Processing dependencies for my-project==0.1
error: Installed distribution distribute 0.6.24dev conflicts with requirement distribute==0.7.3
```

I'm not sure why it's unable to upgrade setuptools from that requirement. Perhaps because distribute/setuptools has already been loaded, so it's considered un-upgradeable.

But what you can do is simply upgrade the setuptools version in the virtualenv before installing your package:

```
$ bin/easy_install -U distribute
Searching for distribute
...
Removing distribute 0.6.24dev from easy-install.pth file
Adding distribute 0.7.3 to easy-install.pth file

Installed /Users/jaraco/issue525/lib/python2.7/site-packages/distribute-0.7.3-py2.7.egg
Processing dependencies for distribute
Searching for setuptools>=0.7
...
Adding setuptools 20.4 to easy-install.pth file
Installing easy_install script to /Users/jaraco/issue525/bin
Installing easy_install-2.7 script to /Users/jaraco/issue525/bin

Installed /Users/jaraco/issue525/lib/python2.7/site-packages/setuptools-20.4-py2.7.egg
Finished processing dependencies for distribute
```

Thereafter, the demo package installs just fine.

I hope that works for you.",{},,User,False
