4408,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-16 16:01:59+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,199266,Ivoz,647025,pypa,229001139,301830019,"Hi, `ssl.PROTOCOL_TLSv1_2` does not exist in python 2.7.3 anyway. Only in 2.7.9 or later.

The new `_SSLContext` infrastructure was patched in 2.7.9 following [pep 466](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0466/) in order to give Python 2 a more reasonable default TLS security story. However it's a rather large change so trying to mix code from before and after like you have attempted is likely to crash and burn in a lot of cases.

I would suggest you upgrade your Python 2 version to the latest patch version.",{},,User,False
