4412,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-20 14:23:50+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,3275593,pradyunsg,647025,pypa,267168451,338221455,"FWIW, I tested this locally:

```
echo ""Setup""
hg clone https://bitbucket.org/pypa/distlib
git clone https://github.com/pypa/pip
git clone https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv
pushd pip
rm -rf pip/_vendor/distlib
cp -r ../distlib/distlib pip/_vendor/
python setup.py bdist_wheel
popd
pushd virtualenv
rm virtualenv_support/pip-9.0.1-py2.py3-none-any.whl
cp ../pip/dist/pip-10.0.0.dev0-py2.py3-none-any.whl virtualenv_support

echo ""Testing""
python ./virtualenv.py 'v e n v' --no-download
source ./v\ e\ n\ v/bin/activate
pip --version
```

If the last command gives 10.0.0.dev0 means all is well. :)
",{},MEMBER,User,False
