5349,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-09 14:27:04+00:00,3274387,RallyTools/RallyRestToolkitForPython,1248618,klehman-rally,1643197,RallyTools,53866229,69340215,"Snarfing from the Chrome Dev tools interface, a search request looks like the following:  https://rally1.rallydev.com/slm/webservice/v2.x/search?pagesize=25&start=1&fetch=true&includePermissions=true&compact=true&project=%2Fproject%2F123456789&projectScopeUp=false&projectScopeDown=true&keywords=wsapi%20documentation&searchScopeOid=987654321&searchScopeUp=false&searchScopeDown=true&searchScopeType=project&recycledItems=true&_slug=%2Fsearch

As it stands now that pyral doesn't expose a 'search' method on the pyral Rally instance that is used for coordinating the request/response interaction with Rally.
The current result by attempting to use the 'get' method results in an error emitting the following:pyral.entity.InvalidRallyTypeNameError: search .
However, it might not be a lot of effort to add 'Search' as a quasi-entity in pyral and provide a 'search' method in the pyral Rally instance to marshal the required elements of the query_string and have some reasonable set of option arguments for the search operation (scoping, inclusion/exclusion of recycle bin items, etc.).
I'll offer no timeframe, but this seems like a useful capability to add to pyral and I'll plan to include this in future work.",{},,User,False
