5879,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-12 12:59:11+00:00,93721432,awslabs/sockeye,2027990,fhieber,3299148,awslabs,273160233,343735552,"@mjdenkowski can give more details on this, but its used for decoding with a reduced vocabulary. 

The way this is implemented is as follows: if reduced vocabulary decoding is used, the inference graphs do not contain the output layer but only return the inputs to it. In beam search, we then call the output layer imperatively using a reduced smaller parameter matrix (HxW) where W << V.
The code you are referring to is called at this point.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
