6268,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-10 14:10:19+00:00,91020334,ni/nimi-python,8085768,marcoskirsch,5598284,ni,339802611,403836321,"Hello.

Per our own [API design guidelines](https://github.com/ni/nimi-python/wiki/API-design-guidelines) and [Zen of Python](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0020/#id3), we removed redundant configuration options. Turns out that the functions you are asking about are nothing more than wrappers around properties.

* Changes were made in #872 
* [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/ni/nimi-python/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md) enumerates the changes.
* You can see documentation for all properties in our [NI Modular Instruments Python Documentation](http://nimi-python.readthedocs.io/en/1.0.0/).

Use:
```
nidcpower.Session.digital_edge_measure_trigger_input_terminal
```
instead of:
```
nidcpower.Session.configure_digital_edge_measure_trigger(input_terminal, edge=nidcpower.DigitalEdge.RISING)
```

Use:
```
nidcpower.Session.exported_measure_trigger_output_terminal
```
instead of:
```
export_signal
```

One piece of functionality we removed is configuring the trigger edge (rising vs falling). We did this after careful consideration because all our SMUs are PXI / PXIe, which per the PXI spec defines triggers going over the trigger bus as rising edge. If this is a problem for your application, we'd love to hear more about it.

I'll close the issue but feel free to re-open or reply if not everything was addressed.",{},MEMBER,User,False
