6652,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-31 14:14:29+00:00,12235583,elastic/curator,1020383,untergeek,6764390,elastic,168513464,236432236,"You're right.  That's not needed for this action to occur.  Curator 4 differs from the previous versions in that it pulls the index metadata for _all_ indices when it starts. The message you report happens during that [index metadata discovery](https://github.com/elastic/curator/blob/master/curator/indexlist.py#L154-L161) step:

```
                    if not 'creation_date' in wl['settings']['index']:
                        self.loggit.warn(
                            'Index: {0} has no ""creation_date""! This implies '
                            'that the index predates Elasticsearch v1.4. For '
                            'safety, this index will be removed from the '
                            'actionable list.'.format(index)
                        )
                        self.__not_actionable(index)
```

As I mentioned already, this is because Curator 4 determines to do the safe thing with older indices.  The [README](https://github.com/elastic/curator#compatibility-matrix) shows that Curator 4 is meant for Elasticsearch versions 2+.  I will add another bit to the README to indicate that indices created before ES 1.4 are not supported. ",{},,User,False
