6729,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-13 18:01:23+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,6014209,yugangw-msft,6844498,Azure,221415253,293976385,"> Would you basically be using just the ""resource"" portion of the arm template to supply to properties?

Close, but not exactly as the command uses resource create API not arm template

help output:
```bash
Command
    az resource create: Create a resource.

Arguments
    --properties -p [Required]: A JSON-formatted string containing resource properties.
    --api-version             : The api version of the resource (omit for latest).
    --id                      : Resource ID.
    --is-full-object          : Indicates that the properties object includes other options such as
                                location, tags, sku, and/or plan.
    --location -l             : Location. You can configure the default location using 'az configure
                                --defaults location=<location>'.
    --name -n                 : The resource name. (Ex: myC).
    --namespace               : Provider namespace (Ex: 'Microsoft.Provider').
    --parent                  : The parent path (Ex: 'resA/myA/resB/myB').
