7141,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-01 16:17:01+00:00,13880738,buildinspace/peru,860932,oconnor663,8107815,buildinspace,95474223,136778614,"Apologies for the lack of detail above. `peru file` is a field that you can include in any module. So for example, you could define:

```yaml
git module my_project:
  url: https://github.com/me/my_project
  peru file: my_peru_file.yaml
```

That would cause peru to read `my_peru_file.yaml` from the root of `my_project` to determine the recursive imports, rather than looking for the usual `peru.yaml` file in there. As a special case of this, you can pass a nonexistent file name here to disable recursive imports entirely.

I'm not a big fan of this design, which is one of the reasons it's not documented yet. The most common use case is the disable-imports-entirely hack, so the design feels backwards. One issue is that so far we've managed to have every field be of the string type, but what we need here looks more like a boolean flag -- something along the lines of `recursive imports: false` -- which requires some more thinking. (Should boolean values silently convert to strings when a string is expected, or should that be an error? Etc.)",{},,User,False
