7194,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-18 07:30:52+00:00,43485399,sods/paramz,1563689,mzwiessele,8537914,sods,326731998,397965763,"You will need to trace the objective and parameters manually. There is two ways of achieving this.
1. You inherit from the model you want to record and overwrite `parameters_changed` function. This function gets called once per iteration. In there you can record the parameters you want to record in an array of sorts. **Make sure you call the `super` `parameters_changed`!**
2. You write a little wrapper around the optimizer, which records the optimization process and then subsequently does the optimization. You will be exposed to the raw optimization array though, so you need to map back to the parameter names.",{},MEMBER,User,False
