7390,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-05 16:51:04+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,6504915,bmw,9289019,letsencrypt,114409228,154119865,"I personally think the opposite and we should call out to `bootstrap/venv.sh`. It makes the code more modular and easier to understand. Since we are currently having `letsencrypt-auto` users clone our entire repo for OS bootstrap scripts, `letsencrypt-auto` calling out to `bootstrap/venv.sh` is not a problem. Furthermore, if we adopt either approach proposed in #1258, calling out to `bootstrap/venv.sh` will still work.",{},,User,False
7401,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-19 10:18:28+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,12718804,TheHades,9289019,letsencrypt,117554296,158014834,"@pde 
Yes, then problem is reproducible.
