7500,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-16 14:15:37+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,1377457,pganssle,9849410,dateutil,308498522,381614370,"This is why we employ [freezegun](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun). [Example use here](https://github.com/dateutil/dateutil/blob/master/dateutil/test/test_utils.py#L18).

You can do something like this:
```python
from freezegun import freeze_time

@freeze_time(datetime(2018, 4, 7, 12, 30))
def test_dtstart_timezone:
    <test goes here>
```

Use pytest style tests instead of the unittest style tests that most of the test suite uses. We're trying to transition over to pytest.",{},OWNER,User,False
