7536,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-22 13:07:17+00:00,43816051,common-workflow-language/cwltool,8131630,kapilkd13,9947495,common-workflow-language,228856900,317182649,"Hi @pvanheus @manu-chroma I think I know the reason behind this behaviour. To evaluate JS expressions we first look for node installation on local system, if we can't find it we intialize Docker Container with node image. 
Since we don't want to wait forever we use a timeout and its default value is 20.  You can use the `--eval-timeout` argument and set a higher timeout. I hope it helps.
P.S  We would recommend cwltool users to install `nodejs` on their local system for best performance.",{},,User,False
