7657,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-13 23:36:52+00:00,14284859,marshmallow-code/marshmallow,3108007,deckar01,10334301,marshmallow-code,165059616,232517588,"A compromise would be for marshmallow to give list errors their own dictionary, so the integer keys are isolated from string keys.

```py
json.dumps({'roles': {'_items': {0: {}}, '_schema': ['Invalid input type.']}}, sort_keys=True)
# '{""roles"": {""_items"": {""0"": {}}, ""_schema"": [""Invalid input type.""]}}'
```

It does seem like a Python bug, because `json.dumps()` is going to cast all the keys to strings anyway. Python could have done this before trying to compare the keys.",{},,User,False
