7760,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-20 04:27:38+00:00,21987374,django-json-api/django-rest-framework-json-api,23664055,emojiface-ops,11215076,django-json-api,221798608,316593293,"@mblayman You're totally right -- so the source of all the queries was pulling the second foreign key (Emoji table joined to EmojiCollection). Instead of just grabbing the id, it joined to the table. So the fix *is* just about making sure only the foreign key ID is returned (i.e. emoji_id).",{},,User,False
7761,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-18 18:34:43+00:00,21987374,django-json-api/django-rest-framework-json-api,913526,benjaminlong,11215076,django-json-api,189344417,366536682,"Hello ! if the community thinks is the good improvement, I will have some time to work on this in the next month. Let me know if there are any first thoughts/ideas. 
