8221,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-15 03:23:52+00:00,34271922,fugue/credstash,5217963,Caid11,13857002,fugue,124852075,171862001,"@bhourigan Ah, I tested it on my personal machine (a.k.a. a machine with no IAM credentials and a boto config file), so that might be the problem. I think I know how to fix the bug; I'll test it tomorrow and submit a PR if it works. 

On the precedence of profiles, I believe that method parameters override all other parameters, so if you create a session with a region, then specify a region as a parameter in a method called on that session, that parameter would override the session parameter (the documentation [here](http://boto3.readthedocs.org/en/latest/guide/configuration.html#configuration-sources) kind of implies this, but doesn't explicitly state it).

On `region_name` not being present in the documentation, I actually noticed that too. It's a pretty common parameter in many other boto methods (clients, sessions, etc.), so I think it might just have been overlooked. However, it might be good to suggest switching `region_name` to the `Session` method just so credstash conforms to the documentation.",{},,User,False
