8634,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-18 21:33:54+00:00,63484632,facebookresearch/fastText,10478219,EdouardGrave,16943930,facebookresearch,342463588,406081500,"Hi @Sandy4321,

We decided to keep the casing when training these models for several reasons. First, for some words, such as `Apple` and `apple`, the capitalized and non-capitalized words are likely referring to different things, and therefore, should have different representations. Second, in some NLP pipelines, the words are not lowercased, and it is therefore important to also have a representation for capitalized words (in order to avoid out-of-vocabulary words).

