8791,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-07 11:07:51+00:00,4198043,ArduPilot/MAVProxy,1731976,stephendade,17919847,ArduPilot,230371445,306763215,">That's due to the mode change confirmation from APM coming in after the new line is printed. I'll see if I can hunt down a method to dynamically re-write the prompt.

Fixed in the latest commit

>Ahh, I expect autotest.py is expecting a differently formatted output. I'll wrangle with autotest.py and see what it expects and patch things to fit.

So, after some very painful wrangling I've discovered that autotest.py is pushing text input too fast. Such that the MAVProxy prompt can't interpret and process all the commands.

So we have 2 options:
-Patch autotest.py to add a delay when sending commands. Specifically line 253 of ./Tools/autotest/pysim/util.py from ``ret.delaybeforesend = 0`` to ``ret.delaybeforesend = 0.1``
-Add a new commandline param to MAVProxy ``--noprompt`` which tells MAVProxy to use the old readline instead of the new CLI prompt. Autotest.py would need to be patched to use this param when calling MAVProxy.

I've tested both options and either works quite nicely. The 2nd option gives less garbage in the autotest output, but does requires that MAVProxy and APM are patched at the same time.

Any preference @peterbarker and @tridge ?",{},,User,False
