8798,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-03 10:37:22+00:00,51361989,FPGAwars/apio,2227572,Jesus89,18257418,FPGAwars,301553531,370137586,"Hi @rdwrt.

The main packages for apio are not available for `linux_armv6l` yet:
- [Toolchain-icestorm](https://github.com/FPGAwars/toolchain-icestorm)
- [Toolchain-iverilog](https://github.com/FPGAwars/toolchain-iverilog)
- [Tools-system](https://github.com/FPGAwars/tools-system)

We need to build all these packages for `linux_armv6l` in order to have support for this architecture in apio.

I created several branches to start with it but I couldn't test it since I haven't got an RPi Zero. Also it seems that it is not trivial to build source code for `linux_armv6l`. If you want to try the builds, here you have the branches:
- [Toolchain-icestorm linux-armv6l branch](https://github.com/FPGAwars/toolchain-icestorm/tree/linux-armv6l)
- [Toolchain-iverilog linux-armv6l branch](https://github.com/FPGAwars/toolchain-iverilog/tree/linux-armv6l)
- [Tools-system linux-armv6l branch](https://github.com/FPGAwars/tools-system/tree/linux-armv6l)

If you have good results in cross-compiling these packages let me know in this ticket or with a PR contribution :)

Thanks!
",{},OWNER,User,False
