8866,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-10 16:05:33+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,239226116,314153216,My concerns were addressed so it's all fine by me.,{},,User,False
8873,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-25 22:16:00+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,245384269,317889298,"@hackaugusto 
Because of the situation that the test of the first commit tests for which is what I believe lead to the situation reported in issue #784.

The Rest API call to register a token uses `manager_address_if_token_registered()` to determine if the token is already registered. If it is it returns the `409` error, but if at the same time the token was registered by another node and not by us then we would not have registered the channel manager and also populated the tokens list. 

We now avoid this by the additional 2 lines in the `manager_address_if_token_registered()` function.

You can recreate the scenario by removing those lines and running the `test_second_manager_address_if_token_registered()` test that this PR adds.",{},,User,False
