9037,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-06 16:24:34+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,249517,robertnishihara,22125274,ray-project,254615203,327538147,"So, we definitely build pyarrow when building Ray. `ray/python/setup.py` calls `ray/build.sh`, which calls `ray/src/thirdparty/build_thirdparty.sh`, which builds pyarrow.

However, it does not ""install"" pyarrow, so it won't add pyarrow to your PYTHONPATH.

However, when we import ray, we manually add it to your PYTHONPATH, see below

https://github.com/ray-project/ray/blob/953878364ec5d19b7563f1597f5631558c4b916a/python/ray/__init__.py#L9-L11

The goal here was to avoid interferring with people's existing pyarrow installations. Although in the future, we'd like to not even compile pyarrow ourselves but rather to just get it from PyPI.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
